name: rule_documentation_presence_for_sch_c_business
question: Is documentation present for borrowers Sch C business

steps.name: step_documentation_check
steps.expert_instructions:
1. From the application_date, extract application_year in the form. Save it as computed_application_year in the form(YYYY)
   From the current_employer.start_date (or "1b Start Date"), extract start_year in the form YYYY and save it as employement_start_year

2. Classify the Application Date into these categories:
   - early_year: 01/01/{computed_application_year} ≤ application_date < 04/14/{computed_application_year}
   - mid_year: 04/15/{computed_application_year} ≤ application_date < 10/14/{computed_application_year}
   - late_year: 10/15/{computed_application_year} ≤ application_date ≤ 12/31/{computed_application_year}
   - full_year: 01/01/{computed_application_year} ≤ application_date ≤ 12/31/{computed_application_year}

3. Check the difference between start date and application date and classify it into these:
   - long_tenured: current_employer.start_date ≤ application_date − 5 years
   - mid_tenured: (application_date − 5 years) < current_employer.start_date ≤ (application_date − 2 years)
   - recently_hired: current_employer.start_date ≥ (application_date − 2 years)

4. Decision Flow: (make sure all the checks are done on seperate subtasks)

   IF (early_year AND long_tenured) THEN  
      Skip to Step 5  

   IF (mid_year AND long_tenured) THEN  
      Skip to Step 6  

   IF (late_year AND long_tenured) THEN  
      Skip to Step 7  

   IF (early_year AND mid_tenured) THEN  
      Skip to Step 8  

   IF (mid_year AND mid_tenured) THEN  
      Skip to Step 9  

   IF (late_year AND mid_tenured) THEN  
      Skip to Step 10  

   IF (early_year AND recently_hired AND start_year == {computed_application_year}-2) THEN  
      Skip to Step 11  

   IF (full_year AND recently_hired AND start_year == {computed_application_year}-2) THEN  
      Skip to Step 11  

   IF (full_year AND recently_hired AND start_year == {computed_application_year}-1) THEN  
      Skip to Step 12  

   IF (None above)  
      Raise DISCREPANCY MESSAGE: "None of the conditions passed for the rule 'Is documentation present for borrower's S-Corporation business?'"

---

5.  
   IF (  
      (ALL OF:  
         From List of Tax Form 1040, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-1,  
         From List of Tax Form 1040, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120S, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-1,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120S, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120SSCHK1, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-1,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120SSCHK1, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2  
      ) OR  
      (ALL OF:  
         From List of Tax Form 1040, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2,  
         From List of Tax Form 1040, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-3,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120S, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120S, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-3,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120SSCHK1, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120SSCHK1, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-3  
      )  
   ) THEN  
      LOG Passed Result:  
      "Borrower's personal Tax Returns (1040s) and Business Tax Returns (1120S) are present for the most recent year. The business is in existence for five years as reflected on Form 1003." and terminate the process
   ELSE  
      RAISE DISCREPANCY MESSAGE:  
      "Borrower's personal Tax Returns (1040s) and/or Business Tax Returns (1120S) are missing for the most recent year. As the business is in existence for five years as reflected on Form 1003." and terminate the process

---

6.  
   IF (  
      (ALL OF:  
         From List of Tax Form 1040, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-1,  
         From List of Tax Form 1040, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120S, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-1,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120S, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-2,  
         From List of Tax Form 1120SSCHK1, if one exists for the year {computed_application_year}-1,

      ) OR

      LOG Passed Result:  
      "Borrower's personal Tax Returns (1040s) and Business Tax Returns (1120S) are present for the most recent year. Required extensions (Form 4868 and/or Form 7004) are also present." and terminate the process
   ELSE  
      RAISE DISCREPANCY MESSAGE:

Form 4868 and/or Form 7004 is missing, which is required if tax returns are unavailable. subtasks.description: Classify the application_date into one of the categories: early_year, mid_year, late_year, or full_year. Use the computed_application_year (from Task 1.a) to build boundary dates as follows: early_year: from 01/01/{computed_application_year} to before 04/14/{computed_application_year}; mid_year: from 04/15/{computed_application_year} to before 10/14/{computed_application_year}; late_year: from 10/15/{computed_application_year} to 12/31/{computed_application_year}; full_year: spanning from 01/01/{computed_application_year} through 12/31/{computed_application_year}. The function should compare the application_date against these boundaries and assign the appropriate classification.

outputs: 'application_date_classification': A string representing the category (early_year, mid_year, late_year, full_year)

subtasks.description: Determine the employment tenure by comparing the application_date and the current_employer.start_date. Based on the difference in years, classify the tenure as follows: long_tenured if current_employer.start_date is at least 5 years earlier than application_date; mid_tenured if start_date is between (application_date - 5 years) and (application_date - 2 years); recently_hired if start_date is within the last 2 years relative to application_date.
formulas: Compute the difference in years between application_date and current_employer.start_date and then apply the thresholds: difference >= 5 years -> long_tenured; 2 years < difference < 5 years -> mid_tenured; difference <= 2 years -> recently_hired.
outputs: 'employment_tenure_classification': A string indicating if the employment is long_tenured, mid_tenured, or recently_hired

Check that from the list of Tax Form 1040, one exists for each of the years (computed_application_year-1) and (computed_application_year-2), and similarly verify for Tax Form 1120S and Tax Form 1120SSCHK1 for the same years based on an OR grouping of two sets of conditions. The business is in existence for five years as reflected on Form 1003." Otherwise, raise a discrepancy using the message: "Borrower's personal Tax Returns (1040s) and/or Business Tax Returns (1120S) are missing for the most recent year. As the business is in existence for five years as reflected on Form 1003." In either case, terminate the process after this check.
